items.name: Bloodborne (PS4)

Face your fears as you search for answers in the ancient city of Yharnam, now cursed with a strange endemic illness spreading through the streets like wildfire. items.name: Canon PG-210 XL Black Inkjet Print Cartridge
items.shortDescription: <p>Canon PG210XL is a popular replacement printer ink cartridge. To get high quality printing the Canon PG-210XL Black Inkjet Print Cartridge must be used with the inkjet printers of this same company. It lasts much longer than the simple 210 cartridge. This Canon print cartridge contains nearly 66 percent more ink than the latter. The actual yield, which is the number of prints that a single cartridge will produce, depends on the type of printing being done. If there are more bold letters, big titles, thick black lines and bullets then more ink is used up. The amount of ink usage also depends on the mode that is selected in your printing options. A fast print option takes up less ink. The quality of the paper on which the printing is done is also important. The Canon PG-210XL Black Inkjet Print Cartridge gives a low level signal when nearly half of it has been used up.</p>
items.longDescription: After inserting a new cartridge a test printing for alignment must be carried out. items.shortDescription: The Elder Scrolls Online is set in Tamriel's Second Era, roughly 1,000 years before the events in The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim and the coming of the Dragonborn, and just before the rise of Tiber Septim, the first Emperor of Tamriel. Three Alliances have emerged across the continent, each struggling for supremacy over the land. As these great powers battle one another for control of the Imperial City - and with it all of Tamriel - darker forces are moving to destroy the world! Journey across the far reaches of ancient Tamriel for the first time since The Elder Scrolls: Arena. From the mountains of Skyrim, to the mysterious lands of Morrowind, to the sprawling metropolis of Daggerfall, experience the wonders of the world a millennium before the events of Oblivion and Skyrim.
